 \frac{1}{N}+3=\frac{2R+2}{5R+2}
 N=\frac{aR+b}{cR+d}
3
\begin{align} \frac{1}{N}+3=\frac{2R+2}{5R+2} &\iff  \frac{1}{N} =\frac{2R+2}{5R+2} -3 \\ \\ & \iff  \dfrac 1N = \dfrac{(2R+2) - 3(5R+2)}{5R + 2} \\ \\ & \iff \frac 1N = \frac{-13 R- 4}{5R + 2}\end{align}
\iff N =\frac {5R + 2}{-13 R- 4} = \frac {-5R - 2}{13 R + 4} =-\frac {5R + 2}{13 R+  4}
